---
description: Prevent high-frequency Canvas/WebGL-like values from using React state
alwaysApply: true
---

# High-Frequency State Restriction

Use this ESLint fragment:

```json
{
  "plugins": ["react"],
  "rules": {
    "no-restricted-syntax": [
      "error",
      {
        "selector": "VariableDeclarator[id.name=/mouse|scroll|position|coordinates/i] > CallExpression[callee.name='useState']",
        "message": "High-frequency data should bypass React state. Use mutable useRefs and direct DOM/Canvas manipulation to avoid VDOM thrashing."
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

Prefer `useRef` + imperative updates for pointer, scroll, and coordinate streams.
